{
  "name": "choirloft",
  "description": "Warm human voices singing oo and ah, angelic and bright — sunlight through stained glass. Soft additive vocal pads with formant warmth and gentle vibrato, ooh and ahh layered: a grounding bass-voice hum, a soprano ooh swelling in over the radiant melody, an alto ahh harmonizing a counter-line, a sweet tenor mmm in the middle, a pure boy-soprano ping, breathy high vocal sparkles, a full layered choir-bloom, a shimmering chorused vocal cluster, the soft intake-of-breath texture of a choir loft, and a joyful little angelic chirp. A major @ A=432, additive and warm, choir/angelic but joyful and major — radiant and human, never mournful.",
  "drone": null,
  "master_gain": 0.45,
  "drone_gain": 0.0,
  "reverb_scale": 1.0,
  "phrase_roots": [9, 4],
  "scale_pitches": [57, 59, 61, 62, 64, 66, 68, 69, 71, 73, 74, 76, 78, 80, 81],
